TEXT.0: This ionogram was digitized from the original ISIS 1 analog

TEXT.1: telemetry data on 7-track tape using the facilities of the Data

TEXT.2: Evaluation Laboratory at GSFC (Code 500). This data restoration

TEXT.3: project is headed by Dr. R.F. Benson (GSFC, Code 673). Ionograms were

TEXT.4: digitized at the rate of 40,000 16-bit samples/sec. This sample rate is

TEXT.5: higher than the Nyquist frequency of 30 kHz. The sample frequency of 40

TEXT.6: kHz provides a measurement every 25 microseconds corresponding to an

TEXT.7: apparent range (c*t/2) interval of 3.747 km. Each ionogram consists

TEXT.8: of a fixed-frequency and and a swept-frequency portion. The time

TEXT.9: resolution is typically 24 seconds. More information can be found
